            <div class="section" id="welcome-to-the-official-typo3-documentation">
                <span id="start"></span>
                <h1>Welcome to the official TYPO3 Documentation<a class="headerlink"
                                                                  href="#welcome-to-the-official-typo3-documentation"
                                                                  title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a>
                </h1>
                <p>TYPO3 CMS is an Open Source Enterprise Content Management System powered by
                    PHP.</p>
                <ul class="horizbuttons-primary-m simple">
                    <li><a class="reference internal"
                           href="Home/GuidesAndTutorials.html#tutorials"><span class="std std-ref">Tutorials and Guides</span></a>
                    </li>
                    <li><a class="reference internal" href="Home/References.html#references"><span
                                    class="std std-ref">Core Documentation</span></a></li>
                    <li><a class="reference internal" href="Home/Extensions.html#extensions"><span
                                    class="std std-ref">Extensions by Extension Key</span></a></li>
                </ul>
                <hr class="docutils"/>
                <div class="section" id="getting-started">
                    <span id="start-getting-stared"></span>
                    <h2>Getting Started<a class="headerlink" href="#getting-started"
                                          title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
                    <ul class="simple">
                        <li>Follow the <a class="reference external"
                                          href="m/typo3/guide-installation/10.4/en-us/QuickInstall/Composer/Index.html#install-via-composer"
                                          title="(in Installation and Upgrade Guide v10.4)"><span
                                        class="xref std std-ref">quick installation guide</span></a>
                            to install TYPO3 using Composer.
                        </li>
                        <li>The <a class="reference external"
                                   href="m/typo3/tutorial-getting-started/10.4/en-us/Index-2.html#start"
                                   title="(in Getting Started Tutorial v10.4)"><span>Getting Started Tutorial</span></a>
                            introduces you to TYPO3’s backend - the interface
                            used for managing content and configuring your TYPO3 installation.
                        </li>
                        <li>Add a domain, set up languages and configure URL handling with the
                            <a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/SiteHandling/Basics.html#sitehandling-basics"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span class="xref std std-ref">site configuration</span></a>
                            tutorial.
                        </li>
                        <li>Additional resources are available in the <a class="reference internal"
                                                                         href="Home/GuidesAndTutorials.html#tutorials"><span
                                        class="std std-ref">Tutorials and Guides</span></a> section.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Support is available via StackOverflow and Slack. Visit the <a
                                class="reference external" href="https://typo3.org/help">help page</a> for
                        more information.</p>
                    <p>For information about the different versions of TYPO3 and its system
                        requirements, visit <a class="reference external" href="https://get.typo3.org/">https://get.typo3.org</a>.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="section" id="how-the-documentation-is-organized">
                    <span id="id1"></span>
                    <h2>How the documentation is organized<a class="headerlink"
                                                             href="#how-the-documentation-is-organized"
                                                             title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a>
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="simple">
                        <li><a class="reference internal" href="Home/GuidesAndTutorials.html#tutorials"><span
                                        class="std std-ref">Tutorials and Guides</span></a> contain a
                            comprehensive list of
                            resources for both new and existing users of TYPO3 including documentation
                            for editors, integrators and developers.
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference internal" href="Home/References.html#references"><span
                                        class="std std-ref">Core Documentation</span></a> features detailed
                            information about TYPO3’s core and is
                            intended for integrators and developers.
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference internal"
                               href="Home/SystemExtensions.html#system-extensions"><span
                                        class="std std-ref">System Extensions</span></a> provide a list of all
                            extensions currently used in
                            TYPO3’s core along with documentation for each of the extensions listed.
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference internal" href="Home/Extensions.html#extensions"><span
                                        class="std std-ref">Extensions by Extension Key</span></a> allow you to
                            search for documentation that has been
                            provided for third party extensions.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="section" id="templating-with-fluid">
                    <span id="start-theme"></span>
                    <h2>Templating with Fluid<a class="headerlink" href="#templating-with-fluid"
                                                title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
                    <p>TYPO3 uses Fluid as its templating engine. Fluid acts as the glue between your
                        HTML templates and the content you create in TYPO3. You can find out more about
                        templating and where to get started by visiting the <a
                                class="reference external"
                                href="m/typo3/tutorial-templating/master/en-us/index.html">Templating
                            Tutorial.</a></p>
                    <ul class="simple">
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/master/en-us/ApiOverview/BackendLayout/Index.html#be-layout">Backend
                                Layouts</a>
                            join the content you create in TYPO3 to specific points in your HTML
                            templates. With backend layouts we are able to map our content to selected
                            points in our HTML where we wish to display our content.
                        </li>
                        <li>The <a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/TYPO3/Fluid"
                                   rel="nofollow noopener">Fluid repository</a> contains further
                            information about Fluid. As it is an independent project, the documentation
                            is not maintained on docs.typo3.org.
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/master/en-us/ApiOverview/ContentElements/AddingYourOwnContentElements.html#adding-your-own-content-elements">Custom
                                content elements</a>
                            give us the ability to create our own custom content types.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="section" id="manage-your-templates-and-more-with-sitepackages">
                    <h2>Manage your templates and more with Sitepackages<a class="headerlink"
                                                                           href="#manage-your-templates-and-more-with-sitepackages"
                                                                           title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a>
                    </h2>
                    <p><a class="reference external"
                          href="https://www.slideshare.net/benjaminkott/typo3-the-anatomy-of-sitepackages"
                          rel="nofollow noopener">Sitepackages</a>
                        allow you to bundle your Fluid templates and other site assets into a single,
                        reusable extension that can be installed with a single click.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="section" id="develop-custom-extensions">
                    <span id="start-extdev"></span>
                    <h2>Develop custom extensions<a class="headerlink" href="#develop-custom-extensions"
                                                    title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
                    <p><a class="reference internal" href="Home/References.html#references"><span
                                    class="std std-ref">Core Documentation</span></a> lists all relevant core
                        manuals. One of these is
                        <a class="reference external"
                           href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/Index-2.html#start"
                           title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>TYPO3 Explained</span></a>. It
                        contains detailed information for core and extension
                        developers,</p>
                    <p>Getting started with extension development:</p>
                    <ul class="simple">
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ExtensionArchitecture/Introduction/Index.html#extension-architecture-introduction"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span class="xref std std-ref">Introduction to extensions in TYPO3</span></a>
                        </li>
                        <li>Extension <a class="reference external"
                                         href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ExtensionArchitecture/FilesAndLocations/Index.html#extension-files-locations"
                                         title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>Files and Locations</span></a>
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ExtensionArchitecture/NamingConventions/Index.html#extension-naming"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>Naming Conventions</span></a>
                            and <a class="reference external"
                                   href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/CodingGuidelines/Index.html#cgl"
                                   title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>Coding Guidelines</span></a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>More topics can be found in <a class="reference external"
                                                      href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/Index-2.html#start"
                                                      title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>TYPO3 Explained</span></a>,
                        for example:</p>
                    <ul class="simple">
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.html#database-query-builder"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span class="xref std std-ref">QueryBuilder</span></a>
                            based on Doctrine
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/DependencyInjection/Index.html#dependencyinjection"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>Dependency Injection</span></a>
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/RequestHandling/Index.html#request-handling"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>Request Handling (Middlewares)</span></a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>If you are updating TYPO3 to the next major version, you may need to make
                        changes in your custom extensions.</p>
                    <p>The <a class="reference external"
                              href="c/typo3/cms-core/master/en-us/index.html">Core changelog</a>
                        lists all relevant changes for each TYPO3 version since 7.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="section" id="configure-your-typo3-installation">
                    <span id="start-configuration"></span>
                    <h2>Configure your TYPO3 installation<a class="headerlink"
                                                            href="#configure-your-typo3-installation"
                                                            title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a>
                    </h2>
                    <p>TYPO3 is well known for being extensive and easy to configure. The
                        <a class="reference external"
                           href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/Configuration/ConfigurationOverview.html#config-overview"
                           title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span>Configuration overview</span></a> in
                        <a class="reference external"
                           href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/Index-2.html#start"
                           title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span class="xref std std-ref">TYPO3 Explained</span></a>
                        gives you an overview of the various configuration options available to you.</p>
                    <ul class="simple">
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/reference-coreapi/10.4/en-us/ApiOverview/SiteHandling/Basics.html#sitehandling-basics"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Explained v10.4)"><span class="xref std std-ref">Site Handling and Configuration</span></a>
                            shows you how
                            to setup domains, languages, human-readable URLs and error pages.
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/tutorial-getting-started/10.4/en-us/UserManagement/Index.html#user-management"
                               title="(in Getting Started Tutorial v10.4)"><span
                                        class="xref std std-ref">Backend User Management</span></a> explains how
                            you
                            setup backend users and grant them specific access to your installation of
                            TYPO3.
                        </li>
                        <li>The <a class="reference external"
                                   href="c/typo3/cms-form/master/en-us/QuickStartForIntegrators/Index.html#quickstartintegrators"
                                   title="(in Form Framework vlatest (10-dev))"><span
                                        class="xref std std-ref">Form system extension</span></a> is a powerful
                            tool that gives backend users the ability to create web forms.
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/tutorial-typoscript-in-45-minutes/10.4/en-us/Index-2.html#start"
                               title="(in TypoScript in 45 Minutes v10.4)"><span
                                        class="xref std std-ref">TypoScript in 45 Minutes</span></a> introduces
                            you to TypoScript,
                            TYPO3’s very own configuration language. TypoScript is used to configure the
                            rendering of web pages, navigation menus, page content and much more.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
