                               href="m/typo3/guide-contributionworkflow/master/en-us/HandlingAPatch/Index.html#improving-a-patch"
                               title="(in TYPO3 Contribution Guide - Core Development v1.0)"><span
                                        class="xref std std-ref">Review patches</span></a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="section" id="contribute-to-official-documentation">
                    <span id="start-contribute-docs"></span>
                    <h2>Contribute to official documentation<a class="headerlink"
                                                               href="#contribute-to-official-documentation"
                                                               title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a>
                    </h2>
                    <p>You are welcome to click on the “Edit on GitHub” button on any page to propose
                        a change in the official documentation whenever you see something that you
                        think can be improved.</p>
                    <ul class="simple">
                        <li>The blog post <a class="reference external"
                                             href="https://typo3.com/blog/start-improving-docs-now-to-grow-typo3">Start
                                Improving Docs Now to Grow TYPO3</a> gives a
                            good introduction to documentation contribution.
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/docs-how-to-document/master/en-us/WritingDocsOfficial/Index.html#docs-contribute"
                               title="(in Writing Documentation v0.0)"><span>How to contribute to official documentation</span></a>
                            explains the workflow for contributing.
                        </li>
                        <li>The documentation is edited in text files using reStructuredText syntax. Use
                            the <a class="reference external"
                                   href="m/typo3/docs-how-to-document/master/en-us/WritingReST/CheatSheet.html#rest-cheat-sheet"
                                   title="(in Writing Documentation v0.0)"><span>reST &amp; Sphinx cheat sheet</span></a>
                            to lookup most commonly used directives.
                        </li>
                        <li>General conventions can be found in <a class="reference external"
                                                                   href="m/typo3/docs-how-to-document/master/en-us/GeneralConventions/Index.html#conventions"
                                                                   title="(in Writing Documentation v0.0)"><span>Documentation content style guide</span></a>
                        </li>
                        <li><a class="reference external"
                               href="m/typo3/docs-how-to-document/master/en-us/WritingDocsOfficial/HowYouCanHelp.html#docs-official-how-you-can-help"
                               title="(in Writing Documentation v0.0)"><span>How You Can Help</span></a>
                            lists some general tasks to
                            get you started.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
